headline: Carnival rises as cruise operator beats profit estimates, reinstates dividend
summary: Investing.com -- Carnival Corporation & plc (NYSE:CCL) reported stronger-than-expected fourth quarter earnings on Friday, beating analyst estimates and announcing the reinstatement of its dividend as the cruise operator achieved investment-grade leverage metrics.

headline: Carnival: Fiscal Q4 Earnings Snapshot
summary: MIAMI (AP) — Carnival Corp. CCL) on Friday reported fiscal fourth-quarter profit of $422 million. On a per-share basis, the Miami-based company said it had profit of 31 cents.
